title: For Sale:  C Sharps 1874 Bridgeport 45-110
postcontent: I am posting up my C Sharps made 1874 Sharps model bridgeport combined with a Malcolm style scope as made by MVA using Creedmoor style mounts. Both companies are based in the state of Montana, and both have an excellent reputation of quality and precision. This rifle is chambered in what many would call the best of precision long range cartridges for BPCR shooting. The Venerable 45-110. I will be including 80 pieces of brass as well as the mould for the highest ranked Paper Patched bullet amongst competitive BPCR shooters. The "Money Bullet". The mould was built under the brand name of Buffalo Arms and sold exclusively through their onlibe store. The mould does not include handles which allows the caster the option to choose what grip will work best for them. There will be a few other supplies going with this, since I will have no need of them. Including though not limited to two jars of 1.5 f black powder.This rifle cost me about $2200, The scope and mounts were over $1000, The various pieces I will be adding in with it are worth near $500. I have not put a single round through it, and the condition is near perfect.I am selling this machine not entirely voluntary. I feell guilty about having it, now knowing that I will never shoot it. I cannot have a safe queen rifle. But I do not have the kinda of dedication and patience to properly clean and maintain a black powder cartridge rifle. That is part of why I do not have the handles for the mould yet, or any lead to send along with it. I know and accept the possibility that this may end up never fired, but I cannot be directly responsible for that. What the new owner uses the machine for is not my business.This rifle has a lack of aesthetic decoration. Instead you will fibd a heavy 34" barrel and an upgraded double set trigger. Before all else this rifle was built to shoot, and to win. I am open to partial trades. I am most interested in milsurp weapons in the 30-06 or 7.62 flavor. Though I have a special place for anything begining with a 6.5 or 303. I will always be in the need of more reloading and gunsmithing tools and supplies. With a good enough offer I may consider a full trade.Email me at mekkaviking at gmail dot com for more photos or any questions.I am convincing myself to sell this beautiful machine. I am not likely to shoot it at any point, though it represents a good chunk of my time and money. I drooled over this rifle and scope combination literally for years before fi ally buying one. It took nine months waiting for C Sharps in Big Timber, Montana to complete this machine. Add another three months waiting for the scope and mounts ro be buolt by MVA, also in Montana. Most firearms enthusiasts have a dream rifle or pistol they wish they could have. This was my obsession. I read every piece of literature I could find on this machine, watched every video, spent countless hours emailing and calling experts to get every bit of detail. Please keep this in mind when making an offer.

title: For Sale:  .556 840 rounds Federal Lake CityTracers
postcontent: This 5.56x45mm M196 tracer ammo loaded on 10 round stripper clips from the famed Lake City plant and is perfect for shooting with your 5.56x45mm chambered AR-15, Mini 14 and other .556 platforms!  Tracer ammo is a great training tool for shooting in low light situations. Many serious shooters find that shooting with tracer ammo is a fun experience and a great training tool. You can actually watch the bullet's flight path through the air with your naked eye! M196 55 gr tracer ammo is actually preferred by many civilian shooters over the more commonly found M856 64 gr tracer load. The reason for this preference is that this projectile will stabilize in a broader range of barrels from 1:9 to 1:12 while the M856 projectile is properly stabilized with only a quick twisting 1:7 twist rate which is less common. If you're unsure, just check your AR-15's barrel and the twist rate will be displayed. If you see a 1:9 or 1:12, then you're good to go!  This ammo comes pre-loaded on 10 round stripper clips which make it super quick to load magazines with. Additionally, the stripper clips loaded in sleeves come in more portable bandoleers for easy toting back and forth to the range. Whether you're looking to do some serious low light training or target practice, Lake City's M196 5.56x45mm ammo is a great option!  Each round is brass-cased, boxer-primed, non-corrosive, and reloadable. It is both economical and precision manufactured in the United States by an established U.S. cartridge producer.EMAIL ME OR TEXT REDACTED
